1
00:00:00,801 --> 00:00:10,389
Subtitles by: Reklame11

2
00:02:37,084 --> 00:02:39,701
The hills are alive

3
00:02:39,996 --> 00:02:44,184
With the sound of music

4
00:02:44,442 --> 00:02:46,775
With songs they have sung

5
00:02:47,065 --> 00:02:51,701
For a thousand years

6
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:54,992
The hills fill my heart

7
00:02:55,222 --> 00:02:59,564
With the sound of music

8
00:02:59,830 --> 00:03:06,702
My heart wants to sing
Every song it hears

9
00:03:07,188 --> 00:03:11,855
My heart wants to beat like the wings
Of the birds that rise

10
00:03:12,114 --> 00:03:15,048
From the lake to the trees

11
00:03:15,249 --> 00:03:19,373
My heart wants to sigh
Like a chime that flies

12
00:03:19,632 --> 00:03:23,407
From a church on a breeze

13
00:03:23,664 --> 00:03:27,011
To laugh like a brook
When it trips and falls

14
00:03:27,246 --> 00:03:30,594
Over stones on its way

15
00:03:30,861 --> 00:03:34,571
To sing through the night

16
00:03:34,829 --> 00:03:38,438
Like a lark who is learning to pray

17
00:03:38,762 --> 00:03:44,162
I go to the hills

18
00:03:44,361 --> 00:03:50,273
When my heart is lonely

19
00:03:50,535 --> 00:03:54,244
I know I will hear

20
00:03:54,437 --> 00:03:58,747
What I've heard before

21
00:03:59,012 --> 00:04:03,552
My heart will be blessed

22
00:04:03,781 --> 00:04:11,230
With the sound of music

23
00:04:12,257 --> 00:04:17,209
And I'll sing...

24
00:04:17,408 --> 00:04:26,004
...once more

25
00:08:56,439 --> 00:09:01,192
Hallelujah, hallelujah

26
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:05,931
Hallelujah, hallelujah

27
00:09:08,050 --> 00:09:10,024
- Reverend Mother.
- Sister Bernice.

28
00:09:10,258 --> 00:09:12,778
- I simply cannot find her.
- Maria?

29
00:09:13,808 --> 00:09:15,052
She's missing again.

30
00:09:15,951 --> 00:09:18,221
We should've put a cowbell
around her neck.

31
00:09:18,447 --> 00:09:21,382
Have you tried the barn? You know
how much she adores the animals.

32
00:09:21,647 --> 00:09:24,264
I have looked everywhere.
In all of the usual places.

33
00:09:24,461 --> 00:09:26,600
Sister, considering it's Maria...

34
00:09:26,894 --> 00:09:29,379
...I suggest you look in someplace
unusual.

35
00:09:34,443 --> 00:09:35,688
Well, Reverend Mother...

36
00:09:35,947 --> 00:09:38,402
...I hope this new infraction ends
whatever doubts...

37
00:09:38,665 --> 00:09:41,764
...you may still have
about Maria's future here.

38
00:09:41,961 --> 00:09:45,856
I always try to keep faith
in my doubts, Sister Berthe.

39
00:09:46,088 --> 00:09:48,837
After all, the wool of a black sheep
is just as warm.

40
00:09:49,063 --> 00:09:53,219
We are not talking about sheep,
black or white, Sister Margaretta.

41
00:09:53,446 --> 00:09:56,741
Of all the candidates for
the novitiate, Maria is the least...

42
00:09:56,997 --> 00:09:59,384
Children, children.

43
00:09:59,844 --> 00:10:03,640
We were speculating about
the qualifications of our postulants.

44
00:10:04,260 --> 00:10:07,129
The Mistress of Novices
and the Mistress of Postulants...

45
00:10:07,362 --> 00:10:12,445
...were trying to help me
by expressing opposite points of view.

46
00:10:12,672 --> 00:10:15,607
Tell me, Sister Catherine,
what do you think of Maria?

47
00:10:15,809 --> 00:10:18,742
She's a wonderful girl,
some of the time.

48
00:10:19,678 --> 00:10:22,647
- Sister Agatha?
- It's very easy to like Maria...

49
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:25,300
...except when it's difficult.

50
00:10:25,598 --> 00:10:29,011
- And you, Sister Sophia?
- Oh, I love her very dearly.

51
00:10:29,212 --> 00:10:32,026
But she always seems to be
in trouble, doesn't she?

52
00:10:32,250 --> 00:10:33,777
Exactly what I say.

53
00:10:34,236 --> 00:10:36,602
She climbs a tree and scrapes her knee

54
00:10:36,795 --> 00:10:38,420
Her dress has got a tear

55
00:10:39,066 --> 00:10:43,057
She waltzes on her way to Mass
And whistles on the stair

56
00:10:43,673 --> 00:10:47,981
And underneath her wimple
She has curlers in her hair

57
00:10:48,247 --> 00:10:52,654
I've even heard her singing
In the abbey

58
00:10:52,887 --> 00:10:54,796
She's always late for chapel

59
00:10:55,031 --> 00:10:57,200
But her penitence is real

60
00:10:57,460 --> 00:10:59,696
She's always late for everything

61
00:10:59,924 --> 00:11:01,866
Except for every meal

62
00:11:02,226 --> 00:11:06,732
I hate to have to say it
But I very firmly feel

63
00:11:06,963 --> 00:11:11,216
Maria's not an asset to the abbey

64
00:11:11,698 --> 00:11:14,085
I'd like to say a word in her behalf

65
00:11:14,352 --> 00:11:15,629
Say it, Sister Margaretta.

66
00:11:16,463 --> 00:11:20,260
Maria makes me laugh

67
00:11:23,023 --> 00:11:26,795
How do you solve a problem like Maria?

68
00:11:27,052 --> 00:11:30,697
How do you catch a cloud
And pin it down?

69
00:11:30,988 --> 00:11:34,185
How do you find a word
That means Maria?

70
00:11:34,698 --> 00:11:35,746
A flibbertigibbet

71
00:11:35,979 --> 00:11:37,255
- A will-o'-the-wisp
- A clown

72
00:11:38,826 --> 00:11:42,401
Many a thing you know
You'd like to tell her

73
00:11:42,663 --> 00:11:45,978
Many a thing she ought to understand

74
00:11:46,376 --> 00:11:49,921
But how do you make her stay
And listen to all you say?

75
00:11:50,471 --> 00:11:53,817
How do you keep a wave upon the sand?

76
00:11:54,053 --> 00:11:57,980
How do you solve a problem like Maria?

77
00:11:58,468 --> 00:12:03,770
How do you hold a moonbeam...

78
00:12:03,972 --> 00:12:09,207
...in your hand?

79
00:12:10,242 --> 00:12:13,590
When I'm with her I'm confused
Out of focus and bemused

80
00:12:13,887 --> 00:12:17,183
And I never know exactly where I am

81
00:12:17,375 --> 00:12:20,572
- Unpredictable as weather
- She's as flighty as a feather

82
00:12:20,927 --> 00:12:22,681
- She's a darling
- She's a demon

83
00:12:22,878 --> 00:12:24,153
She's a lamb

84
00:12:24,540 --> 00:12:28,051
She'll out pester any pest
Drive a hornet from its nest

85
00:12:28,252 --> 00:12:31,415
She can throw a whirling dervish
Out of whirl

86
00:12:31,964 --> 00:12:35,345
- She is gentle, she is wild
- She's a riddle, she's a child

87
00:12:35,898 --> 00:12:38,352
- She's a headache
- She's an angel

88
00:12:38,552 --> 00:12:42,294
She's a girl

89
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:46,775
How do you solve a problem like Maria?

90
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:50,544
How do you catch a cloud
And pin it down?

91
00:12:50,839 --> 00:12:54,185
How do you find a word
That means Maria?

92
00:12:54,453 --> 00:12:56,362
- A flibbertigibbet
- A will-o'-the-wisp

93
00:12:56,597 --> 00:12:58,156
A clown

94
00:12:58,611 --> 00:13:02,190
Many a thing you know
You'd like to tell her

95
00:13:02,452 --> 00:13:05,799
Many a thing she ought to understand

96
00:13:06,003 --> 00:13:10,158
- But how do you make her stay
- And listen to all you say?

97
00:13:10,386 --> 00:13:14,313
How do you keep a wave upon the sand?

98
00:13:14,512 --> 00:13:20,108
How do you solve a problem like Maria?

99
00:13:35,402 --> 00:13:41,893
How do you hold a moonbeam...

100
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:48,902
...in your hand?

101
00:14:00,229 --> 00:14:02,136
You may go in now, Maria.

102
00:14:14,209 --> 00:14:15,768
Come here, my child.

103
00:14:22,014 --> 00:14:23,321
Now sit down.

104
00:14:24,220 --> 00:14:27,635
Reverend Mother, I'm sorry.
I couldn't help myself.

105
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:30,746
- The hills were beckoning and before...
- Dear.

106
00:14:31,130 --> 00:14:33,018
I haven't summoned you for apologies.

107
00:14:33,243 --> 00:14:35,381
Please let me ask for forgiveness.

108
00:14:36,025 --> 00:14:37,203
If you'll feel better.

109
00:14:38,104 --> 00:14:40,374
Yes, you see,
the sky was so blue today...

110
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:44,244
...and everything was so green and
fragrant, I had to be a part of it.

111
00:14:44,505 --> 00:14:48,813
The Untersberg led me higher like
it wanted me to go through the clouds.

112
00:14:49,014 --> 00:14:50,956
Suppose darkness had come
and you were lost?

113
00:14:51,221 --> 00:14:53,360
Mother, I could never be lost
up there.

114
00:14:53,620 --> 00:14:56,338
That's my mountain.
I was brought up on it.

115
00:14:56,532 --> 00:14:58,736
It was the mountain that led me
to you.

116
00:14:59,476 --> 00:15:02,322
When I was a child,
I would come down and climb a tree...

117
00:15:02,578 --> 00:15:04,268
...and look in your garden.

118
00:15:04,498 --> 00:15:07,313
I'd see the sisters at work
and hear them sing.

119
00:15:08,593 --> 00:15:12,073
Which brings me to another
transgression, Reverend Mother.

120
00:15:12,272 --> 00:15:14,345
I was singing out there today.

121
00:15:14,992 --> 00:15:18,853
Only in the abbey do we have rules
about postulants singing.

122
00:15:19,054 --> 00:15:20,995
I can't stop wherever I am.

123
00:15:21,198 --> 00:15:23,432
Worse, I can't seem to stop
saying things.

124
00:15:23,693 --> 00:15:25,865
Everything I think and feel.

125
00:15:26,092 --> 00:15:27,466
Some call that "honesty."

126
00:15:27,724 --> 00:15:29,993
Oh, but it's terrible,
Reverend Mother!

127
00:15:30,188 --> 00:15:33,928
You know how Sister Berthe makes me
kiss the floor after a disagreement?

128
00:15:34,282 --> 00:15:37,631
Lately, I kiss the floor
when I see her coming to save time.

129
00:15:40,202 --> 00:15:41,314
Maria...

130
00:15:42,281 --> 00:15:45,150
...when you saw us over the wall
and longed to be with us...

131
00:15:45,383 --> 00:15:49,920
...that didn't mean you were prepared
for the way we live here, did it?

132
00:15:51,205 --> 00:15:53,506
No, Mother, but I pray and I try.

133
00:15:53,701 --> 00:15:55,360
And I am learning. I really am.

134
00:15:55,589 --> 00:15:58,141
What is the most important lesson
you have learned here?

135
00:15:58,788 --> 00:16:02,431
To find out what is the will of God
and do it wholeheartedly.

136
00:16:05,154 --> 00:16:06,233
Maria...

137
00:16:07,682 --> 00:16:10,332
...it seems to be God's will
that you leave us.

138
00:16:10,592 --> 00:16:12,021
- Leave?
- Only for a while.

139
00:16:12,512 --> 00:16:14,749
No, Mother!
Please don't send me away!

140
00:16:14,976 --> 00:16:19,066
This is where I belong. It's my home,
my family. It's my life.

141
00:16:19,709 --> 00:16:22,612
- Are you truly ready for it?
- Yes, I am.

142
00:16:22,811 --> 00:16:27,514
If you go out into the world for a
time, knowing what we expect of you...

143
00:16:27,772 --> 00:16:30,389
...you will find out
if you can expect it of yourself.

144
00:16:30,586 --> 00:16:34,710
I know what you expect, Mother,
and I can do it! I promise I can!

145
00:16:38,106 --> 00:16:39,283
Yes, Mother.

146
00:16:41,305 --> 00:16:42,897
If it is God's will.

147
00:16:45,048 --> 00:16:49,965
There is a family near Salzburg that
needs a governess until September.

148
00:16:50,166 --> 00:16:52,305
- September?
- For seven children.

149
00:16:52,950 --> 00:16:53,898
Seven children?!

150
00:16:54,132 --> 00:16:55,342
Do you like children?

151
00:16:56,085 --> 00:16:57,839
Well, yes, but seven!

152
00:16:58,931 --> 00:17:01,963
I will tell Captain von Trapp
to expect you tomorrow.

153
00:17:02,482 --> 00:17:03,824
Captain?

154
00:17:04,498 --> 00:17:09,134
A retired officer of the Imperial
Navy. A fine man and a brave one.

155
00:17:09,362 --> 00:17:11,979
His wife died,
and he is alone with the children.

156
00:17:12,176 --> 00:17:16,297
I understand he has had a difficult
time keeping a governess there.

157
00:17:17,038 --> 00:17:19,242
Why difficult, Reverend Mother?

158
00:17:20,556 --> 00:17:23,371
The Lord will show you
in His own good time.

159
00:17:58,724 --> 00:18:01,090
When the Lord closes a door...

160
00:18:01,283 --> 00:18:03,705
...somewhere He opens a window.

161
00:18:05,954 --> 00:18:10,743
What will this day be like?

162
00:18:10,944 --> 00:18:13,082
I wonder

163
00:18:19,325 --> 00:18:23,253
What will my future be?

164
00:18:24,060 --> 00:18:26,231
I wonder

165
00:18:27,739 --> 00:18:30,706
It could be so exciting

166
00:18:30,907 --> 00:18:33,873
To be out in the world
To be free

167
00:18:34,073 --> 00:18:37,009
My heart should be wildly rejoicing

168
00:18:38,137 --> 00:18:43,252
Oh, what's the matter with me?

169
00:18:43,575 --> 00:18:46,509
I've always longed for adventure

170
00:18:46,773 --> 00:18:50,189
To do the things I've never dared

171
00:18:50,421 --> 00:18:53,487
Now here I'm facing adventure

172
00:18:53,781 --> 00:18:59,628
Then why am I so scared?

173
00:19:02,930 --> 00:19:05,713
A captain with seven children

174
00:19:05,938 --> 00:19:08,653
What's so fearsome about that?

175
00:19:11,088 --> 00:19:13,607
I must stop these doubts and worries

176
00:19:13,870 --> 00:19:16,586
If I don't I just know I'll turn back

177
00:19:16,845 --> 00:19:19,880
I must dream of the things
I am seeking

178
00:19:20,909 --> 00:19:25,698
I am seeking the courage I lack

179
00:19:26,572 --> 00:19:30,248
The courage to serve them
With reliance

180
00:19:30,506 --> 00:19:33,290
Face my mistakes without defiance

181
00:19:33,547 --> 00:19:35,171
Show them I'm worthy

182
00:19:35,403 --> 00:19:37,955
And while I show them

183
00:19:38,218 --> 00:19:41,859
I'll show me

184
00:19:42,054 --> 00:19:47,237
So let them bring on
All their problems

185
00:19:47,462 --> 00:19:50,592
I'll do better than my best

186
00:19:50,853 --> 00:19:53,788
I have confidence
They'll put me to the test

187
00:19:54,020 --> 00:19:57,315
But I'll make them see
I have confidence in me

188
00:19:57,538 --> 00:20:00,669
Somehow I will impress them

189
00:20:00,930 --> 00:20:04,029
I will be firm but kind

190
00:20:04,291 --> 00:20:07,453
And all those children
Heaven bless them

191
00:20:07,681 --> 00:20:10,844
They will look up to me
And mind me

192
00:20:11,071 --> 00:20:14,070
With each step I am more certain

193
00:20:14,334 --> 00:20:17,467
Everything will turn out fine

194
00:20:17,694 --> 00:20:20,660
I have confidence
The world can all be mine

195
00:20:20,894 --> 00:20:26,107
They'll have to agree
I have confidence in me

196
00:20:27,611 --> 00:20:30,229
I have confidence in sunshine

197
00:20:30,491 --> 00:20:33,457
I have confidence in rain

198
00:20:33,690 --> 00:20:36,440
I have confidence
That spring will come again

199
00:20:36,731 --> 00:20:39,630
Besides which you see
I have confidence in me

200
00:20:39,927 --> 00:20:42,861
Strength doesn't lie in numbers

201
00:20:43,126 --> 00:20:46,029
Strength doesn't lie in wealth

202
00:20:46,263 --> 00:20:49,458
Strength lies in nights
Of peaceful slumbers

203
00:20:49,717 --> 00:20:52,466
When you wake up, wake up
It's healthy

204
00:20:52,756 --> 00:20:55,625
All I trust I leave my heart to

205
00:20:55,860 --> 00:20:58,640
All I trust becomes my own

206
00:20:58,834 --> 00:21:03,438
I have confidence in confidence alone

207
00:21:17,454 --> 00:21:19,013
Oh, help.

208
00:21:30,699 --> 00:21:37,090
I have confidence in confidence alone

209
00:21:37,863 --> 00:21:42,466
Besides which you see
I have confidence...

210
00:21:42,726 --> 00:21:49,249
...in me

211
00:21:55,524 --> 00:21:57,826
Hello. Here I am.

212
00:22:00,547 --> 00:22:02,303
I'm from the convent.
I'm the new governess, captain.

213
00:22:03,906 --> 00:22:07,003
And I'm the old butler, fraulein.

214
00:22:08,895 --> 00:22:10,619
Well, how do you do?

215
00:22:20,701 --> 00:22:24,594
You'll wait here, please.

216
00:23:47,398 --> 00:23:51,325
In future, remember certain rooms
in this house are not to be disturbed.

217
00:23:52,452 --> 00:23:53,859
Yes, captain, sir.

218
00:24:01,473 --> 00:24:06,490
- Why do you stare at me that way?
- You don't look like a sea captain.

219
00:24:07,647 --> 00:24:10,582
I'm afraid you don't look
very much like a governess.

220
00:24:11,263 --> 00:24:12,277
- Turn around.
- What?

221
00:24:12,606 --> 00:24:13,817
Turn.

222
00:24:16,862 --> 00:24:17,974
Hat off.

223
00:24:21,054 --> 00:24:23,574
Put on another dress
before meeting the children.

224
00:24:23,868 --> 00:24:25,363
But I don't have another.

225
00:24:25,627 --> 00:24:28,376
When we enter the abbey,
our worldly clothes go to the poor.

226
00:24:28,603 --> 00:24:29,813
What about this one?

227
00:24:30,009 --> 00:24:31,285
The poor didn't want it.

228
00:24:33,048 --> 00:24:36,396
There wasn't time to make a new dress.
I can make clothes.

229
00:24:37,624 --> 00:24:39,796
I'll see that you get some material.

230
00:24:40,504 --> 00:24:41,965
Today, if possible.

231
00:24:42,903 --> 00:24:44,593
- Now, fraulein...
- Maria.

232
00:24:44,821 --> 00:24:47,440
I don't know how much
the abbess told you.

233
00:24:47,702 --> 00:24:50,155
You are the twelfth governess...

234
00:24:50,357 --> 00:24:52,724
...to look after my children
since their mother died.

235
00:24:52,917 --> 00:24:55,056
I trust you will be an improvement
on the last one.

236
00:24:55,284 --> 00:24:57,038
She stayed only two hours.

237
00:24:58,676 --> 00:25:01,161
What's wrong with the children, sir?

238
00:25:02,577 --> 00:25:06,798
Nothing is wrong with the children,
only the governesses.

239
00:25:07,056 --> 00:25:11,790
They could not maintain discipline,
without which the house cannot be run.

240
00:25:12,685 --> 00:25:14,409
Drill them in their studies.

241
00:25:14,637 --> 00:25:17,985
I will not permit them to dream
away their summer holidays.

242
00:25:18,252 --> 00:25:20,837
Each afternoon,
they march, breathing deeply.

243
00:25:21,036 --> 00:25:22,629
Bedtime is to be strictly observed.

244
00:25:22,828 --> 00:25:23,757
When do they play?

245
00:25:23,949 --> 00:25:27,842
You will see to it that they conduct
themselves with the utmost decorum.

246
00:25:28,075 --> 00:25:30,888
- I am placing you in command.
- Yes, sir.

247
00:26:48,212 --> 00:26:49,325
Now...

248
00:26:49,909 --> 00:26:52,723
...this is your new governess,
Fraulein Maria.

249
00:26:54,323 --> 00:26:56,231
Give your name at your signal.

250
00:26:56,531 --> 00:27:00,555
Fraulein, listen carefully. Learn
their signals so you can call them.

251
00:27:01,809 --> 00:27:03,116
Liesl.

252
00:27:03,376 --> 00:27:05,035
Friedrich.

253
00:27:05,297 --> 00:27:06,757
Louisa.

254
00:27:07,024 --> 00:27:08,233
Kurt.

255
00:27:08,463 --> 00:27:09,478
Brigitta.

256
00:27:09,743 --> 00:27:10,919
Marta.

257
00:27:17,038 --> 00:27:18,314
Gretl.

258
00:27:22,764 --> 00:27:26,057
Now, let's see how well you listened.

259
00:27:26,281 --> 00:27:28,551
I won't need to whistle for them,
Reverend Captain.

260
00:27:28,810 --> 00:27:32,126
I mean, I'll use their names.
Such lovely names.

261
00:27:32,329 --> 00:27:35,362
Fraulein, this is a large house.
The grounds are extensive.

262
00:27:35,592 --> 00:27:38,242
And I will not have anyone shouting.

263
00:27:38,471 --> 00:27:40,130
You will take this, please.
Learn to use it.

264
00:27:40,327 --> 00:27:41,920
The children will help you.

265
00:27:43,877 --> 00:27:47,706
Now, when I want you,
this is what you will hear.

266
00:27:48,549 --> 00:27:50,272
Oh, no, sir. I'm sorry, sir!

267
00:27:51,109 --> 00:27:52,601
I could never answer to a whistle.

268
00:27:52,804 --> 00:27:55,322
Whistles are for animals,
not for children.

269
00:27:55,586 --> 00:27:57,561
And definitely not for me.

270
00:27:57,793 --> 00:28:00,313
It would be too humiliating.

271
00:28:01,090 --> 00:28:06,074
Fraulein, were you this much trouble
at the abbey?

272
00:28:06,369 --> 00:28:07,414
Oh, much more, sir.

273
00:28:18,076 --> 00:28:19,571
I don't know your signal.

274
00:28:20,989 --> 00:28:23,507
You may call me "captain."

275
00:28:35,897 --> 00:28:37,302
At ease.

276
00:28:39,990 --> 00:28:41,483
Now that there's just us...

277
00:28:41,750 --> 00:28:45,744
...would you please tell me all your
names again and how old you are.

278
00:28:46,198 --> 00:28:50,027
I'm Liesl. I'm 16 years old,
and I don't need a governess.

279
00:28:50,773 --> 00:28:53,705
I'm glad you told me, Liesl.
We'll just be good friends.

280
00:28:55,793 --> 00:28:59,405
I'm Friedrich. I'm 14.
I'm impossible.

281
00:28:59,697 --> 00:29:01,291
Really? Who told you that, Friedrich?

282
00:29:01,554 --> 00:29:04,902
Fraulein Josephine.
Four governesses ago.

283
00:29:05,328 --> 00:29:06,734
I'm Brigitta.

284
00:29:08,494 --> 00:29:12,323
You didn't tell me how old you are,
Louisa.

285
00:29:12,974 --> 00:29:15,146
I'm Brigitta. She's Louisa.

286
00:29:15,374 --> 00:29:18,024
She's 13 years old, and you're smart.

287
00:29:18,252 --> 00:29:21,862
I'm 10, and I think your dress
is the ugliest one I ever saw.

288
00:29:22,187 --> 00:29:24,706
- Brigitta, you shouldn't say that.
- Why not?

289
00:29:24,907 --> 00:29:27,076
- Don't you think it's ugly?
- Of course.

290
00:29:27,337 --> 00:29:29,922
But Fraulein Helga's was ugliest.

291
00:29:30,186 --> 00:29:32,673
I'm Kurt. I'm 11.
I'm incorrigible.

292
00:29:32,936 --> 00:29:35,936
- Congratulations.
- What's "incorrigible"?

293
00:29:36,168 --> 00:29:39,875
I think it means you want
to be treated like a boy.

294
00:29:41,958 --> 00:29:45,121
I'm Marta, and I'm going to be
seven on Tuesday.

295
00:29:45,381 --> 00:29:46,691
I'd like a pink parasol.

296
00:29:47,844 --> 00:29:49,306
Pink's my favorite color too.

297
00:29:51,618 --> 00:29:52,731
Yes, you're Gretl.

298
00:29:53,603 --> 00:29:55,227
And you're five years old?

299
00:29:55,649 --> 00:29:57,559
My, you're practically a lady.

300
00:29:59,969 --> 00:30:02,870
I have to tell you a secret.
I've never been a governess.

301
00:30:04,257 --> 00:30:06,906
You don't know anything
about being a governess?

302
00:30:07,167 --> 00:30:08,476
Nothing. I'll need lots of advice.

303
00:30:09,407 --> 00:30:13,748
The best way to start is to tell
Father to mind his own business.

304
00:30:13,949 --> 00:30:15,672
Never come to dinner on time.

305
00:30:15,869 --> 00:30:18,072
Never eat your soup quietly.

306
00:30:18,716 --> 00:30:20,723
During dessert, always blow your nose.

307
00:30:20,955 --> 00:30:23,638
Don't you believe a word they say,
Fraulein Maria.

308
00:30:23,834 --> 00:30:27,062
- Oh, why not?
- Because I like you.

309
00:30:27,835 --> 00:30:29,742
Children, outside for your walk.

310
00:30:29,945 --> 00:30:31,767
Father's orders. Hurry up.

311
00:30:31,961 --> 00:30:33,204
Quick, quick, quick.

312
00:30:33,432 --> 00:30:36,498
Fraulein Maria, I'm Frau Schmidt,
the housekeeper.

313
00:30:36,726 --> 00:30:37,740
How do you do.

314
00:30:37,942 --> 00:30:40,723
I'll show you to your room.
Follow me.

315
00:30:51,347 --> 00:30:53,037
Poor little dears.

316
00:31:05,232 --> 00:31:09,420
You're very lucky. With
Fraulein Helga it was a snake.

317
00:31:22,699 --> 00:31:23,974
Good evening.

318
00:31:25,354 --> 00:31:28,769
- Good evening, children.
- Good evening, Fraulein Maria.

319
00:31:35,687 --> 00:31:37,247
Enchanting little ritual.

320
00:31:37,446 --> 00:31:40,064
Something you learned at the abbey?

321
00:31:41,224 --> 00:31:43,459
No.

322
00:31:45,029 --> 00:31:46,239
Rheumatism.

323
00:31:55,650 --> 00:31:58,682
Excuse me, captain. Haven't we
forgotten to thank the Lord?

324
00:32:06,559 --> 00:32:09,406
For what we receive,
may the Lord make us truly thankful.

325
00:32:09,920 --> 00:32:11,774
- Amen.
- Amen.

326
00:32:16,125 --> 00:32:17,978
I'd like to thank you all...

327
00:32:18,171 --> 00:32:21,040
...for the precious gift
you left in my pocket today.

328
00:32:24,411 --> 00:32:26,134
What gift?

329
00:32:29,114 --> 00:32:31,186
It's a secret between
the children and me.

330
00:32:31,449 --> 00:32:34,927
Then I suggest you keep it,
and let us eat.

331
00:32:35,287 --> 00:32:37,173
Knowing how nervous
I must have been...

332
00:32:37,399 --> 00:32:39,734
...a stranger in a new household...

333
00:32:39,926 --> 00:32:42,860
...knowing how important it was
for me to feel accepted...

334
00:32:43,126 --> 00:32:47,149
...it was so kind and thoughtful of
you to make my first moments here...

335
00:32:47,411 --> 00:32:49,516
...so warm and happy...

336
00:32:49,715 --> 00:32:51,404
...and pleasant.

337
00:33:00,273 --> 00:33:02,214
- What is the matter, Marta?
- Nothing.

338
00:33:14,124 --> 00:33:15,105
Fraulein...

339
00:33:15,339 --> 00:33:19,016
...is it to be at every meal
or merely at dinnertime...

340
00:33:19,243 --> 00:33:23,618
...that you intend leading us through
this rare and wonderful new world...

341
00:33:23,819 --> 00:33:25,411
...of indigestion?

342
00:33:26,921 --> 00:33:29,670
They're all right, captain.
They're just happy.

343
00:33:47,652 --> 00:33:50,204
- Rolfe, good evening.
- Good evening, Franz.

344
00:33:50,467 --> 00:33:53,085
- I trust everything is under control?
- Yes, yes.

345
00:33:54,658 --> 00:33:56,991
- Are there any developments?
- Perhaps.

346
00:33:57,185 --> 00:33:59,256
- Is the captain home?
- He's at dinner.

347
00:33:59,488 --> 00:34:01,725
- With the family?
- Yes.

348
00:34:01,983 --> 00:34:03,706
Give him this telegram at once.

349
00:34:04,416 --> 00:34:05,464
Certainly.

350
00:34:16,667 --> 00:34:18,293
A telegram for you, sir.

351
00:34:21,019 --> 00:34:22,775
Franz? Who delivered it?

352
00:34:23,066 --> 00:34:25,008
That young lad Rolfe, of course.

353
00:34:27,257 --> 00:34:28,915
Father, may I be excused?

354
00:34:29,848 --> 00:34:34,125
Children, in the morning I shall
be going to Vienna.

355
00:34:34,424 --> 00:34:36,758
Not again, Father!

356
00:34:40,501 --> 00:34:42,475
How long will you be gone this time?

357
00:34:43,092 --> 00:34:44,499
I'm not sure, Gretl.

358
00:34:44,691 --> 00:34:48,105
- To visit Baroness Schraeder again?
- Mind your own business!

359
00:34:49,042 --> 00:34:50,897
As a matter of fact, yes, Louisa.

360
00:34:52,594 --> 00:34:56,270
- Why can't we ever see the baroness?
- Why would she want to see you?

361
00:34:56,562 --> 00:35:01,230
You are going to see the baroness.
I'm bringing her back with me to visit.

362
00:35:02,671 --> 00:35:04,396
And Uncle Max.

363
00:35:04,656 --> 00:35:06,956
Uncle Max!

364
00:35:22,346 --> 00:35:23,623
Rolfe!

365
00:35:26,569 --> 00:35:27,583
Oh, Rolfe!

366
00:35:30,024 --> 00:35:32,839
- No, Liesl. We mustn't!
- Why not, silly?

367
00:35:33,064 --> 00:35:35,616
- I don't know...
- Isn't this why you're waiting?

368
00:35:35,847 --> 00:35:37,636
Yes, of course.

369
00:35:37,832 --> 00:35:40,512
- I've missed you, Liesl.
- You have? How much?

370
00:35:40,741 --> 00:35:44,416
I even thought of sending a telegram,
so I'd be able to deliver it here.

371
00:35:44,675 --> 00:35:48,417
Oh, that's a lovely thought!
Why don't you, right now?

372
00:35:48,675 --> 00:35:52,669
- But I'm here!
- Please, Rolfe. Send me a telegram.

373
00:35:52,866 --> 00:35:56,182
I'll start it for you.
"Dear Liesl..."

374
00:35:56,833 --> 00:36:00,312
"Dear Liesl: I'd like to be able
to tell you...

375
00:36:00,545 --> 00:36:02,649
...how I feel about you. Stop.

376
00:36:02,880 --> 00:36:07,222
Unfortunately, this wire
is already too expensive.

377
00:36:07,423 --> 00:36:08,798
Sincerely, Rolfe."

378
00:36:08,991 --> 00:36:11,640
- "Sincerely"?
- Cordially.

379
00:36:11,837 --> 00:36:14,389
- "Cordially"?
- Affectionately?

380
00:36:16,669 --> 00:36:18,609
Will there be any reply?

381
00:36:19,835 --> 00:36:21,907
"Dear Rolfe: Stop.

382
00:36:22,874 --> 00:36:25,841
Don't stop! Your Liesl."

383
00:36:27,514 --> 00:36:31,189
If only we didn't have to wait
for someone to send Father a telegram.

384
00:36:31,448 --> 00:36:33,750
How do I know when I'll see you again?

385
00:36:34,616 --> 00:36:35,759
Well, let's see...

386
00:36:38,646 --> 00:36:40,533
I could come here by mistake.

387
00:36:41,493 --> 00:36:45,933
With a telegram for Colonel Schneider!
He's here from Berlin staying with...

388
00:36:46,804 --> 00:36:49,967
No one knows he's here.
Don't tell your father.

389
00:36:50,228 --> 00:36:53,259
- Why not?
- Your father's so Austrian.

390
00:36:53,458 --> 00:36:54,701
We're all Austrian.

391
00:36:54,897 --> 00:36:59,118
Some think we ought to be German, and
they're very mad at those who don't.

392
00:36:59,344 --> 00:37:01,036
They're getting ready to...

393
00:37:02,639 --> 00:37:04,975
Let's hope your father
doesn't get into trouble.

394
00:37:05,263 --> 00:37:09,963
Don't worry. He's a big naval hero.
He was even decorated by the emperor.

395
00:37:10,157 --> 00:37:13,286
I don't worry about him.
I worry about his daughter.

396
00:37:13,805 --> 00:37:15,212
Me? Why?

397
00:37:15,500 --> 00:37:16,994
- Well, you're so...
- What?

398
00:37:17,419 --> 00:37:18,848
You're such a baby!

399
00:37:19,275 --> 00:37:22,056
I'm 16.
What's such a baby about that?

400
00:37:24,201 --> 00:37:27,584
You wait, little girl
On an empty stage

401
00:37:27,817 --> 00:37:31,046
For fate to turn the light on

402
00:37:31,655 --> 00:37:34,754
Your life, little girl
Is an empty page

403
00:37:35,016 --> 00:37:38,908
That men will want to write on

404
00:37:39,588 --> 00:37:44,858
To write on

405
00:37:45,765 --> 00:37:49,538
You are 16 going on 17

406
00:37:49,730 --> 00:37:53,407
Baby, it's time to think

407
00:37:53,602 --> 00:37:57,081
Better beware
Be canny and careful

408
00:37:57,313 --> 00:38:00,793
Baby, you're on the brink

409
00:38:01,121 --> 00:38:04,796
You are 16 going on 17

410
00:38:04,991 --> 00:38:08,502
Fellows will fall in line

411
00:38:08,797 --> 00:38:11,993
Eager young lads
And roues and cads

412
00:38:12,189 --> 00:38:15,962
Will offer you food and wine

413
00:38:16,220 --> 00:38:19,831
Totally unprepared are you

414
00:38:20,220 --> 00:38:23,633
To face a world of men

415
00:38:24,184 --> 00:38:28,178
Timid and shy and scared are you

416
00:38:28,472 --> 00:38:31,820
Of things beyond your ken

417
00:38:32,023 --> 00:38:35,731
You need someone older and wiser

418
00:38:35,958 --> 00:38:39,665
Telling you what to do

419
00:38:39,892 --> 00:38:43,187
I am 17 going on 18

420
00:38:43,413 --> 00:38:49,128
I'll take care of you

421
00:39:20,330 --> 00:39:23,526
I am 16 going on 17

422
00:39:23,722 --> 00:39:26,983
I know that I'm naive

423
00:39:27,241 --> 00:39:30,339
Fellows I meet
May tell me I'm sweet

424
00:39:30,569 --> 00:39:34,112
And willingly I believe

425
00:39:34,566 --> 00:39:37,598
I am 16 going on 17

426
00:39:37,797 --> 00:39:41,409
Innocent as a rose

427
00:39:41,605 --> 00:39:44,921
Bachelor dandies
Drinkers of brandies

428
00:39:45,219 --> 00:39:48,416
What do I know of those?

429
00:39:48,611 --> 00:39:51,992
Totally unprepared am I

430
00:39:52,258 --> 00:39:55,606
To face a world of men

431
00:39:56,002 --> 00:39:59,197
Timid and shy and scared am I

432
00:39:59,457 --> 00:40:02,967
Of things beyond my ken

433
00:40:03,389 --> 00:40:06,837
I need someone older and wiser

434
00:40:07,069 --> 00:40:10,233
Telling me what to do

435
00:40:10,556 --> 00:40:14,101
You are 17 going on 18

436
00:40:14,332 --> 00:40:19,765
I'll depend on you

437
00:42:08,158 --> 00:42:09,530
Come in.

438
00:42:10,525 --> 00:42:12,084
Frau Schmidt.

439
00:42:14,331 --> 00:42:15,990
For your new dresses.

440
00:42:16,282 --> 00:42:20,110
- The captain had these sent from town.
- Oh, how lovely!

441
00:42:20,379 --> 00:42:23,672
These will make the prettiest
clothes I've ever had.

442
00:42:23,929 --> 00:42:27,278
Do you think he would
get me more material if I asked?

443
00:42:27,510 --> 00:42:30,991
- How many dresses do you need?
- Not for me, for the children.

444
00:42:31,254 --> 00:42:33,228
I want to make them some play clothes.

445
00:42:33,495 --> 00:42:36,877
The von Trapp children don't play.
They march.

446
00:42:37,365 --> 00:42:39,666
Surely you don't approve of that.

447
00:42:40,627 --> 00:42:42,929
Ever since the captain
lost his poor wife...

448
00:42:43,154 --> 00:42:45,740
...he runs this house as if on
one of his ships.

449
00:42:46,546 --> 00:42:47,888
Whistles, orders.

450
00:42:48,147 --> 00:42:49,903
No more music, no more laughing.

451
00:42:50,162 --> 00:42:53,544
Nothing that reminds him of her.
Even the children.

452
00:42:54,033 --> 00:42:55,081
But that's so wrong.

453
00:42:55,889 --> 00:42:57,348
Oh, well.

454
00:42:57,551 --> 00:43:01,062
How do you like your room?
There'll be new drapes at the windows.

455
00:43:01,326 --> 00:43:02,536
Bu these are fine.

456
00:43:02,766 --> 00:43:04,359
New ones have been ordered.

457
00:43:04,559 --> 00:43:07,722
- But I really don't need them.
- Good night, now.

458
00:43:07,950 --> 00:43:11,811
Frau Schmidt, if I asked
the captain about the material?

459
00:43:12,076 --> 00:43:16,351
- He's leaving in the morning.
- Of course. How long will he be gone?

460
00:43:16,906 --> 00:43:21,314
It depends. The last time he visited
the baroness, he stayed for a month.

461
00:43:22,442 --> 00:43:26,815
I shouldn't be saying this to you.
I don't know you that well.

462
00:43:27,080 --> 00:43:29,861
But if you ask me,
the captain's thinking seriously...

463
00:43:30,055 --> 00:43:32,257
...of marrying her before
summer's over.

464
00:43:32,453 --> 00:43:35,551
Wonderful! The children will
have a mother again.

465
00:43:36,934 --> 00:43:38,177
Yes.

466
00:43:38,436 --> 00:43:40,094
Well, good night.

467
00:43:40,292 --> 00:43:41,666
Good night.

468
00:43:59,347 --> 00:44:02,065
Dear Father, now I know
why You sent me here.

469
00:44:02,293 --> 00:44:05,044
To help these children
prepare for a new mother.

470
00:44:05,270 --> 00:44:08,436
And I pray this will become
a happy family in Thy sight.

471
00:44:08,633 --> 00:44:11,634
God bless the captain.
God bless Liesl and Friedrich.

472
00:44:11,835 --> 00:44:15,830
God bless Louisa, Brigitta,
Marta and little Gretl.

473
00:44:16,127 --> 00:44:18,845
And I forgot the other boy.
What's his name?

474
00:44:20,544 --> 00:44:22,301
Well, God bless what's-his-name.

475
00:44:22,498 --> 00:44:26,327
God bless the Reverend Mother
and Sister Margaretta...

476
00:44:26,531 --> 00:44:28,256
...and everybody at the abbey.

477
00:44:28,454 --> 00:44:30,876
And now, dear God, about Liesl.

478
00:44:31,366 --> 00:44:33,188
Help her know that I'm her friend...

479
00:44:33,383 --> 00:44:35,840
...and help her tell me
what she's been up to.

480
00:44:36,552 --> 00:44:37,666
Are you going to tell on me?

481
00:44:37,900 --> 00:44:41,196
Help me to be understanding
so I may guide her footsteps.

482
00:44:41,453 --> 00:44:43,975
In the name of the Father,
the Son and the Holy Ghost.

483
00:44:44,174 --> 00:44:47,046
I was out walking
and somebody locked the doors early.

484
00:44:47,345 --> 00:44:50,825
I didn't want to wake everybody,
so when I saw your window open...

485
00:44:52,402 --> 00:44:55,306
You're not going to tell Father,
are you?

486
00:45:01,144 --> 00:45:02,388
How did you climb up?

487
00:45:02,873 --> 00:45:05,874
It's how we always got in
to play tricks on the governess.

488
00:45:06,076 --> 00:45:08,946
Louisa can make it with
a whole jar of spiders in her hand.

489
00:45:09,917 --> 00:45:11,512
Spiders?

490
00:45:15,073 --> 00:45:17,595
Were you out walking all by yourself?

491
00:45:24,774 --> 00:45:28,321
If we wash that dress tonight,
nobody would notice it tomorrow.

492
00:45:28,969 --> 00:45:30,661
You could put this on.

493
00:45:32,330 --> 00:45:34,917
Take your dress and put it
to soak in the bathtub.

494
00:45:35,148 --> 00:45:38,531
Come back here and sit on the bed,
and we'll have a talk.

495
00:45:39,792 --> 00:45:42,693
I told you today
I didn't need a governess.

496
00:45:42,897 --> 00:45:44,905
Well, maybe I do.

497
00:46:14,147 --> 00:46:16,604
Gretl, are you scared?

498
00:46:19,974 --> 00:46:22,147
You're not frightened
of a storm, are you?

499
00:46:22,376 --> 00:46:24,549
You just stay right here with me.

500
00:46:25,673 --> 00:46:29,735
- Where are the others?
- They're asleep. They're not scared.

501
