752
01:03:59,097 --> 01:04:02,195
...that you brought some meaning back
into my life.

753
01:04:03,964 --> 01:04:06,616
I am amusing, I suppose.

754
01:04:06,845 --> 01:04:11,420
I have the finest couturier in Vienna
and a glittering circle of friends.

755
01:04:11,616 --> 01:04:14,617
- I do give some rather gay parties.
- Oh, yes.

756
01:04:14,850 --> 01:04:16,607
But take all that away...

757
01:04:16,803 --> 01:04:21,060
...and you have just wealthy,
unattached little me...

758
01:04:21,702 --> 01:04:24,006
...searching, just like you.

759
01:04:28,907 --> 01:04:30,533
More strudel, Herr Detweiler?

760
01:04:30,794 --> 01:04:32,258
- How many have I had?
- Two.

761
01:04:32,492 --> 01:04:34,350
Make it an uneven three.

762
01:04:37,518 --> 01:04:40,423
Still eating, Max?
Must be unhappy.

763
01:04:40,625 --> 01:04:44,424
That mixed quartet I've been trying
to steal away from Sol Hurok...

764
01:04:44,660 --> 01:04:47,215
- What happened?
...Sascha Petrie stole them first.

765
01:04:47,445 --> 01:04:48,656
I hate thieves.

766
01:04:48,918 --> 01:04:52,085
Max, you really must try
and learn to love yourself.

767
01:04:52,313 --> 01:04:54,550
I had to call Paris, Rome
and Stockholm.

768
01:04:54,810 --> 01:04:58,227
- On Georg's telephone, of course.
- How else could I afford it?

769
01:04:58,685 --> 01:05:03,608
I like rich people, the way they live
and how I live when I'm with them.

770
01:05:03,935 --> 01:05:05,846
I wonder where the children are.

771
01:05:06,240 --> 01:05:08,631
They must have heard
I was coming and hid.

772
01:05:08,899 --> 01:05:11,290
I was hoping they'd be here
to welcome you.

773
01:05:11,524 --> 01:05:15,835
Max, do step out of character for
a moment and try and be charming.

774
01:05:24,523 --> 01:05:25,866
Well?

775
01:05:26,733 --> 01:05:27,878
Well what?

776
01:05:28,109 --> 01:05:30,892
Have you made up his mind?
Do I hear wedding bells?

777
01:05:31,151 --> 01:05:33,063
- Pealing madly.
- Marvelous.

778
01:05:33,296 --> 01:05:35,948
- Not necessarily for me.
- What kind of talk's that?

779
01:05:36,146 --> 01:05:37,642
None-of-your-business talk.

780
01:05:37,938 --> 01:05:40,275
I'm terribly fond of him,
so don't toy with us.

781
01:05:40,534 --> 01:05:43,983
But I'm a child. I like toys.
So tell me everything.

782
01:05:44,279 --> 01:05:49,139
Come on. Tell me every teensy-weensy,
intimate, disgusting detail.

783
01:05:50,556 --> 01:05:54,517
Well, let's just say I have a feeling
I may be here on approval.

784
01:05:54,749 --> 01:05:57,653
- I approve of that. How can you miss?
- Far too easily.

785
01:05:57,919 --> 01:06:01,020
If I know you, darling,
and I do, you will find a way.

786
01:06:01,282 --> 01:06:03,673
- He's no ordinary man.
- No, he's rich.

787
01:06:03,906 --> 01:06:06,079
His wife's death gave him
a great heartache.

788
01:06:06,276 --> 01:06:09,279
And your husband's death
gave you a great fortune.

789
01:06:09,478 --> 01:06:11,367
Oh, Max, you really are a beast.

790
01:06:11,558 --> 01:06:15,423
You and Georg are like family.
That's why I want to see you married.

791
01:06:15,659 --> 01:06:19,074
We must keep all that lovely money
in the family.

792
01:06:34,709 --> 01:06:37,523
- What are you doing there?
- Oh, Captain von Trapp.

793
01:06:37,782 --> 01:06:39,727
I was just looking for...

794
01:06:40,570 --> 01:06:43,286
I didn't see, I mean,
I didn't know you were...

795
01:06:43,865 --> 01:06:45,493
Heil Hitler!

796
01:06:46,173 --> 01:06:47,601
Who are you?

797
01:06:47,867 --> 01:06:50,009
I have a telegram for Herr Detweiler.

798
01:06:50,269 --> 01:06:52,890
- I am Herr Detweiler.
- Yes, sir.

799
01:06:57,763 --> 01:07:00,250
You've delivered your telegram.
Now get out.

800
01:07:06,760 --> 01:07:10,023
- Georg, he's just a boy.
- Yes, and I'm just an Austrian.

801
01:07:10,250 --> 01:07:12,901
Things will happen.
Make sure they don't happen to you.

802
01:07:13,196 --> 01:07:15,750
Max! Don't you ever say that again.

803
01:07:16,013 --> 01:07:18,118
I have no political convictions.

804
01:07:18,351 --> 01:07:21,167
- Can I help it if other people do?
- You can help it.

805
01:07:22,258 --> 01:07:24,330
You must help it.

806
01:07:34,201 --> 01:07:35,728
Hello?

807
01:07:38,266 --> 01:07:40,918
You're far away. Where are you?

808
01:07:41,212 --> 01:07:44,924
In a world that's disappearing,
I'm afraid.

809
01:07:45,726 --> 01:07:49,177
Is there any way I could bring you
back to the world I'm in?

810
01:08:14,064 --> 01:08:16,454
- Father! Father!
- There's your father!

811
01:08:17,233 --> 01:08:19,756
Oh, captain, you're home!

812
01:08:27,798 --> 01:08:30,353
Come out of that water at once!

813
01:08:39,103 --> 01:08:41,209
Oh, you must be Baroness Schraeder.

814
01:08:46,307 --> 01:08:49,178
I'm soaked to the skin!

815
01:09:00,651 --> 01:09:01,994
Straight line!

816
01:09:16,084 --> 01:09:18,386
This is Baroness Schraeder.

817
01:09:20,886 --> 01:09:22,577
And these...

818
01:09:22,807 --> 01:09:24,335
...are my children.

819
01:09:25,401 --> 01:09:26,832
How do you do?

820
01:09:27,866 --> 01:09:32,409
Go inside, dry off, clean up, change
your clothes and report back here!

821
01:09:37,217 --> 01:09:39,225
Fraulein, you will stay here, please!

822
01:09:40,898 --> 01:09:44,316
I think I'd better go see
what Max is up to.

823
01:09:54,123 --> 01:09:55,815
Now, fraulein...

824
01:09:57,645 --> 01:09:59,621
...I want a truthful answer.

825
01:10:00,014 --> 01:10:01,422
Yes, captain.

826
01:10:01,712 --> 01:10:05,608
Is it possible,
or could I have just imagined it?

827
01:10:07,060 --> 01:10:11,371
Have my children, by any chance,
been climbing trees today?

828
01:10:11,829 --> 01:10:12,943
Yes, captain.

829
01:10:13,974 --> 01:10:15,250
I see.

830
01:10:15,800 --> 01:10:20,112
And where, may I ask,
did they get these...

831
01:10:20,377 --> 01:10:22,354
- Play clothes.
- Is that what they are?

832
01:10:22,556 --> 01:10:25,820
I made them from the drapes
that used to hang in my bedroom.

833
01:10:26,590 --> 01:10:28,631
- Drapes?
- They have plenty of wear left.

834
01:10:28,831 --> 01:10:30,686
We've been everywhere in them.

835
01:10:30,913 --> 01:10:35,191
Are you telling me that my children
have been roaming about Salzburg...

836
01:10:35,395 --> 01:10:38,625
...dressed up in nothing
but some old drapes?

837
01:10:38,852 --> 01:10:40,447
And having a marvelous time!

838
01:10:40,647 --> 01:10:43,747
- They have uniforms.
- Forgive me, straitjackets.

839
01:10:43,977 --> 01:10:46,629
They can't be children
if they worry about clothes...

840
01:10:46,889 --> 01:10:47,971
They don't complain.

841
01:10:48,203 --> 01:10:50,790
They don't dare.
They love you too much and fear...

842
01:10:51,021 --> 01:10:52,517
Don't discuss my children.

843
01:10:52,718 --> 01:10:54,574
You've got to hear, you're
never home...

844
01:10:54,766 --> 01:10:56,227
I don't want to hear more!

845
01:10:56,464 --> 01:10:58,854
I know you don't, but you've got to!

846
01:10:59,602 --> 01:11:01,674
- Liesl's not a child.
- Not one word...

847
01:11:01,939 --> 01:11:04,690
Soon she'll be a woman
and you won't even know her.

848
01:11:04,948 --> 01:11:07,885
Friedrich wants to be a man
but you're not here to show...

849
01:11:08,151 --> 01:11:09,427
Don't you dare tell me...

850
01:11:09,655 --> 01:11:12,788
Brigitta could tell you about him.
She notices everything.

851
01:11:13,017 --> 01:11:16,018
Kurt acts tough to hide the pain
when you ignore him...

852
01:11:16,219 --> 01:11:17,682
...the way you do all of them.

853
01:11:17,949 --> 01:11:20,252
Louisa, I don't know about yet.

854
01:11:20,509 --> 01:11:23,578
The little ones just want love.
Please, love them all.

855
01:11:23,839 --> 01:11:25,302
I don't care to hear more.

856
01:11:25,538 --> 01:11:29,467
- I am not finished yet, captain!
- Oh, yes, you are, captain!

857
01:11:30,948 --> 01:11:32,062
Fraulein.

858
01:11:33,316 --> 01:11:37,281
Now, you will pack
your things this minute...

859
01:11:37,480 --> 01:11:39,871
...and return to the abbey.

860
01:11:42,410 --> 01:11:43,687
What's that?

861
01:11:45,356 --> 01:11:46,339
It's singing.

862
01:11:46,958 --> 01:11:49,641
Yes, I realize it's singing.
But who is singing?

863
01:11:50,576 --> 01:11:52,070
The children.

864
01:11:54,833 --> 01:11:56,110
The children?

865
01:11:56,658 --> 01:11:59,279
I taught them something to sing
for the baroness.

866
01:12:04,696 --> 01:12:10,482
My heart wants to sing
Every song it hears

867
01:12:10,749 --> 01:12:13,204
Every song that it hears

868
01:12:13,469 --> 01:12:18,687
My heart wants to beat like the wings
Of the birds that rise

869
01:12:18,943 --> 01:12:21,945
From the lake to the trees

870
01:12:22,177 --> 01:12:23,553
To the trees

871
01:12:23,780 --> 01:12:28,517
My heart wants to sigh
Like a chime that flies

872
01:12:28,710 --> 01:12:33,153
From a church on a breeze

873
01:12:33,415 --> 01:12:37,161
To laugh like a brook
When it trips and falls

874
01:12:37,419 --> 01:12:40,235
Over stones on its way

875
01:12:40,526 --> 01:12:41,836
On its way

876
01:12:42,062 --> 01:12:46,318
To sing through the night

877
01:12:46,512 --> 01:12:51,949
Like a lark who is learning to pray

878
01:12:52,211 --> 01:12:56,523
I go to the hills

879
01:12:56,726 --> 01:13:02,709
When my heart is lonely

880
01:13:02,972 --> 01:13:06,520
I know I will hear

881
01:13:06,780 --> 01:13:12,317
What I've heard before

882
01:13:13,118 --> 01:13:17,181
My heart will be blessed

883
01:13:17,410 --> 01:13:24,092
With the sound of music

884
01:13:24,933 --> 01:13:29,925
And I'll sing...

885
01:13:30,154 --> 01:13:37,925
...once more

886
01:14:09,859 --> 01:14:11,551
Edelweiss!

887
01:14:15,365 --> 01:14:18,401
You never told me how enchanting
your children are.

888
01:14:26,667 --> 01:14:28,163
Don't go away.

889
01:14:33,072 --> 01:14:34,414
Fraulein.

890
01:14:37,618 --> 01:14:38,763
I...

891
01:14:40,181 --> 01:14:42,865
...behaved badly. I apologize.

892
01:14:44,535 --> 01:14:47,985
I'm far too outspoken.
It's one of my worst faults.

893
01:14:48,376 --> 01:14:49,785
You were right.

894
01:14:52,156 --> 01:14:53,977
I don't know my children.

895
01:14:55,227 --> 01:14:59,192
There's still time, captain.
They want so much to be close to you.

896
01:14:59,518 --> 01:15:03,232
And you brought music back
into the house.

897
01:15:04,514 --> 01:15:05,890
I'd forgotten.

898
01:15:08,517 --> 01:15:09,793
Fraulein.

899
01:15:12,199 --> 01:15:13,410
I want you to stay.

900
01:15:17,257 --> 01:15:19,876
I ask you to stay.

901
01:15:21,644 --> 01:15:24,995
- Lf I could be of any help.
- You have already.

902
01:15:25,583 --> 01:15:26,598
More than you know.

903
01:15:45,530 --> 01:15:46,807
Marta.

904
01:15:47,515 --> 01:15:48,694
Curtain!

905
01:15:51,263 --> 01:15:54,459
High on a hill was a lonely goatherd

906
01:15:55,904 --> 01:15:59,039
Loud was the voice
Of the lonely goatherd

907
01:16:00,483 --> 01:16:03,617
Folks in a town
That was quite remote heard

908
01:16:05,127 --> 01:16:08,227
Lusty and clear
From the goatherd's throat heard

909
01:16:19,277 --> 01:16:22,030
Marta. Marta!

910
01:16:24,338 --> 01:16:26,249
Gretl, the prince!

911
01:16:27,924 --> 01:16:31,242
A prince on the bridge
Of a castle moat heard

912
01:16:32,664 --> 01:16:34,901
Men on a road
With a load to tote heard

913
01:16:37,304 --> 01:16:40,438
Men in the midst
Of a table d'hote heard

914
01:16:41,723 --> 01:16:44,857
Men drinking beer
With the foam afloat heard

915
01:16:55,492 --> 01:16:58,493
One little girl
In a pale pink coat heard

916
01:17:00,071 --> 01:17:03,269
She yodeled back
To the lonely goatherd

917
01:17:04,392 --> 01:17:07,657
Soon her mama
With a gleaming gloat heard

918
01:17:09,098 --> 01:17:12,265
What a duet for a girl and goatherd

919
01:17:56,968 --> 01:18:00,102
One little girl
