922
01:18:10,705 --> 01:18:13,708
What a duet for a girl and goatherd

923
01:18:15,347 --> 01:18:16,910
Happy are they

924
01:18:19,765 --> 01:18:22,897
Soon the duet will become a trio

925
01:18:46,405 --> 01:18:47,932
- Bravo!
- Bravo!

926
01:18:48,134 --> 01:18:49,564
Very good!

927
01:18:51,304 --> 01:18:53,129
Wonderful!

928
01:18:53,706 --> 01:18:56,741
- Can we keep the puppets, Uncle Max?
- Yes, can we?

929
01:18:56,939 --> 01:18:58,883
Of course you may, my darlings.

930
01:18:59,086 --> 01:19:03,146
Why else did I tell Professor Kohner
to send the bill to your father?

931
01:19:06,738 --> 01:19:08,331
Well done, fraulein.

932
01:19:10,739 --> 01:19:12,628
I really am very much impressed.

933
01:19:12,821 --> 01:19:14,730
They're your children, captain.

934
01:19:21,658 --> 01:19:23,863
My dear, is there anything
you can't do?

935
01:19:24,123 --> 01:19:26,361
Well, I'm not sure
I'll make a good nun.

936
01:19:26,588 --> 01:19:29,559
If you have any problems,
I'd be happy to help you.

937
01:19:32,545 --> 01:19:33,920
Attention, everyone!

938
01:19:34,114 --> 01:19:37,432
I have an announcement to make.
Surprise! Surprise!

939
01:19:37,668 --> 01:19:39,872
Today, after a long
and desperate search...

940
01:19:40,134 --> 01:19:44,926
...I have found a most exciting
entry for the Salzburg Folk Festival.

941
01:19:45,127 --> 01:19:46,885
Congratulations, Max.

942
01:19:47,114 --> 01:19:49,962
And who will you
be exploiting this time?

943
01:19:51,692 --> 01:19:54,761
- The Saint Ignatius Choir?
- Guess again.

944
01:19:55,439 --> 01:19:59,215
Well, let me see now.
The Klopmann Choir?

945
01:19:59,441 --> 01:20:01,744
- No, no, no, no.
- No, no?

946
01:20:01,936 --> 01:20:03,083
Tell us.

947
01:20:03,283 --> 01:20:06,601
A singing group all in one family.
You'll never guess, Georg.

948
01:20:06,869 --> 01:20:09,652
What a charming idea!

949
01:20:09,847 --> 01:20:11,571
Whose family?

950
01:20:12,409 --> 01:20:13,969
Yours.

951
01:20:14,169 --> 01:20:16,407
They'll be the talk of the festival.

952
01:20:19,133 --> 01:20:22,002
- Well, now, what's so funny?
- You are, Max.

953
01:20:22,270 --> 01:20:25,273
You're expensive, but very funny.

954
01:20:25,985 --> 01:20:28,222
- They'll be a sensation!
- No, Max.

955
01:20:28,480 --> 01:20:30,587
It's a wonderful idea.
Fresh, original.

956
01:20:30,787 --> 01:20:35,394
Max! My children
do not sing in public.

957
01:20:36,038 --> 01:20:37,926
You can't blame me for trying.

958
01:20:38,119 --> 01:20:40,991
Children, who shall we hear
from next?

959
01:20:43,691 --> 01:20:44,804
Who?

960
01:20:50,735 --> 01:20:51,881
Yes.

961
01:20:54,642 --> 01:20:56,497
The vote is unanimous.

962
01:20:57,297 --> 01:20:58,794
You, captain.

963
01:20:59,060 --> 01:21:00,206
Me?

964
01:21:01,013 --> 01:21:03,219
- I don't understand.
- Please.

965
01:21:09,179 --> 01:21:11,220
No, no, no, no.

966
01:21:11,483 --> 01:21:13,459
I'm told that you were quite good.

967
01:21:13,661 --> 01:21:16,828
- That was a very, very long time ago.
- I remember, Father.

968
01:21:17,055 --> 01:21:19,806
- Play us something we know.
- Oh, please, Father.

969
01:21:22,625 --> 01:21:23,641
Well...

970
01:21:33,481 --> 01:21:35,554
- Why didn't you tell me?
- What?

971
01:21:35,818 --> 01:21:38,021
To bring along my harmonica.

972
01:21:40,269 --> 01:21:42,309
Edelweiss

973
01:21:43,823 --> 01:21:46,027
Edelweiss

974
01:21:47,088 --> 01:21:53,039
Every morning you greet me

975
01:21:53,268 --> 01:21:56,203
Small and white

976
01:21:57,013 --> 01:22:00,245
Clean and bright

977
01:22:00,440 --> 01:22:03,158
You look happy...

978
01:22:03,354 --> 01:22:07,034
...to meet me

979
